The `uart_tick()` method handles TX busy countdown:

```rust
pub fn uart_tick(&mut self) {
    if self.io.uart_never_ready {
        // TX stays busy forever — tests that programs poll before writing
        return;
    }
    if self.io.uart_tx_countdown > 0 {
        self.io.uart_tx_countdown -= 1;
        if self.io.uart_tx_countdown == 0 {
            self.io.uart_tx_busy = false;
        }
    }
}
```

### 7. Dump Functionality

**No dedicated UART dump feature exists.** The codebase only has:

- Simple UART output buffer access: `get_uart_output()` returning the raw string
